article.linkText: Pope scores 13 as Fresno State knocks off San Diego 71-67
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- — Isaiah Pope had 13 points in Fresno State's 71-67 win against San Diego on Friday night. Pope added five rebounds for the Bulldogs (7-6). Eduardo Andre scored 11 points and added five rebounds and four blocks. Xavier Dusell was 4-of-11 shooting (1 for 8 from 3-point range) to finish with 11 points. Deuce Turner led the Toreros (9-5) in scoring, finishing with 25 points. San Diego also got 22 points from Wayne McKinney III. PJ Hayes also had six points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
